The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the areas of algorithms and machine learning. The focus is on stochastic settings, where the input is generated randomly according to some distribution. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The use of decision trees and adaptive algorithms also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information theory and game theory concepts, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) categories.
